liver-cancer-due-to-alcohol-use-cr.def:
This cause includes death and disability resulting from invasive neoplasms of the liver (specifically due to alcohol use), including ICD-10 codes such as C22.0.
There were 98 500 incident cases (95% UI 79 000–120 000), 90 700 deaths (73 300–109 000), and 2·18 million (1·76–2·65) DALYs from liver cancer due to alcohol use globally in 2019.
liver-cancer-due-to-alcohol-use-cr.name: Liver cancer due to alcohol use

liver-cancer-due-to-hepatitis-b-cr.def:

There were 219 000 incident cases (95% UI 186 000–255 000), 192 000 deaths (162 000–224 000), and 5·80 million (4·91–6·77) DALYs from liver cancer due to hepatitis B globally in 2019.
liver-cancer-due-to-hepatitis-b-cr.name: Liver cancer due to hepatitis B

liver-cancer-due-to-hepatitis-c-cr.name: Liver cancer due to hepatitis C

liver-cancer-due-to-nash-cr.def:

liver-cancer-due-to-nash-cr.name: Liver cancer due to NASH

liver-cancer-due-to-other-causes-cr.def:
This cause includes death and disability resulting from invasive neoplasms of the liver (specifically due to causes other than alcohol use, hepatitis B, hepatitis C, or NASH), including ICD-10 codes such as C22.0.
There were 28 500 incident cases (95% UI 23 600–34 100), 25 600 deaths (21 200–30 500), and 876 000 DALYs (749 000–1 020 000) from liver cancer due to other causes globally in 2019.
liver-cancer-due-to-other-causes-cr.name: Liver cancer due to other causes
